snippet.textDisplay: Relatable moment: Homegirl said people ask if she was dating her brother over there and I felt that. I’m a year and a half older than my brother. In high school not a lot of people knew I had a sibling and I don’t know if anyone even considered my brother having one lol. Anyway on several occasions we were walking together (we ran in the same circles, we were in the same club, small school, small town) but still people would be like are you dating. The look of disgust on both of our faces still to this day when someone asks is too real. It’s been five years since the first time someone asked us that and it ain’t got any less gross. WE LOOK ALIKE. Like why would you think that two pale ass brown hair blue eye kids with freckles would be dating before you’d think they’re siblings lmao.

We both wear glasses though, and you could probably tell by putting us together and how we act, because we always argue and fight




Just to be clear we are full siblings, my dad just has red hair and blue eyes and got that, so did my sister, but I got my mom's hair and eyes
